{"comments":"Bezier Evaluation — Point evaluation, tangents, and subdivision.\n\n## Overview\n\nThis module provides functions for evaluating Bezier curves at any\nparameter value t ∈ [0, 1], computing tangent vectors, and subdividing\ncurves into smaller segments.\n\nAll evaluation uses the De Casteljau algorithm for numerical stability.\n\n## De Casteljau Algorithm\n\nRather than directly computing the polynomial form, De Casteljau \nrecursively linearly interpolates between control points. This approach:\n- Is numerically stable even for extreme t values\n- Naturally provides subdivision as a byproduct\n- Is geometrically intuitive\n","declarations":[{"children":[],"comments":"Evaluate quadratic Bezier at parameter t ∈ [0, 1].\n\nUses De Casteljau algorithm for numerical stability.\nB(t) = (1-t)²P0 + 2(1-t)tP1 + t²P2\n","info":{"declType":"value","type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Function"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Number"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Function"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Geometry","Bezier","Types"],"QuadBezier"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Geometry","Point"],"Point2D"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[66,47],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Geometry/Bezier/Evaluation.purs","start":[66,1]},"title":"quadPointAt"},{"children":[],"comments":"Evaluate cubic Bezier at parameter t ∈ [0, 1].\n\nUses De Casteljau algorithm for numerical stability.\nB(t) = (1-t)³P0 + 3(1-t)²tP1 + 3(1-t)t²P2 + t³P3\n","info":{"declType":"value","type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Function"],"tag":"TypeCons